e%20Gen%20X%20was%20a%20journey%20from%20boomer%20to%20millennial%2C%20and%20it%20wasn't%20a%20destination%20at%20any%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jason%20Salmon%2C%20a%20standup%20comic%20whose%20comedy%20often%20focuses%20on%20the%20plight%20of%20Gen%20X.%20Online%2C%20he%20jokes%2C%20younger%20generations%20identify%20themselves%20with%20pronouns%2C%20and%20older%20generations%20do%20flags%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bwe're%20in%20this%20middle%20ground%2C%20where%20there's%20no%20emoji%20for%20concert%20T-shirts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20Gen%20X's%20discourse%20disappearing%20act%20is%20contextual.%20Many%20Gen%20Xers%2C%20famously%2C%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-going-to-school-was-like-throughout-history-2017-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elatchkey%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20often%20left%20to%20their%20own%20devices%20after%20school%20while%20their%20parents%20were%20at%20work.%20They%20grew%20up%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20a%20solid%20time%20for%20the%20US%20economically%2C%20but%20also%20an%20era%20of%20transition%20in%20technology%2C%20politics%2C%20and%20culture.%20They%20idolized%20Luke%20Skywalker%20as%20kids%20and%20then%20came%20of%20age%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmid-life-crisis-visit-kurt-cobain-nirvana-seattle-shrine-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKurt%20Cobain%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20shift%20from%20romantic%20heroism%20to%20grunge%20cynicism.%20Whereas%20boomers%20were%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-baby-boomers-became-the-most-selfish-generation-2016-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eme%20generation%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20millennials%20were%20the%20%26quot%3Bme%20me%20me%20generation%2C%26quot%3B%20Gen%20X%20has%20become%20the%20%26quot%3Bmeh%26quot%3B%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20historically%20have%20wanted%20to%20kind%20of%20fly%20under%20the%20radar%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Erin%20Mantz%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Gen%20X%20Girls%20Grow%20Up%2C%20a%20blog%20and%20Facebook%20group%20for%20Gen%20X%20women.%20%26quot%3BWe%20kind%20of%20were%20like%2C%20'Whatever.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20X's%20%26quot%3Bwhatever%26quot%3B%20attitude%20has%20translated%20to%20a%20society%20that's%20perpetually%20a%20little%20%26quot%3Bwhatever%26quot%3B%20about%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20called%20up%20Megan%20Gerhardt%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20leadership%20and%20management%20at%20Miami%20University%20who's%20a%20Gen%20Xer%20herself%2C%20to%20ask%20for%20her%20take%20on%20the%20whole%20forgotten%20generation%20thing%2C%20I%20floated%20the%20idea%20that%20maybe%20a%20lot%20of%20it%20was%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fmidlife-crisis%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emiddle%20age%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Gen%20X%20right%20now%20is%2044%20to%2060%2C%20in%20the%20throes%20of%20what's%20supposed%20to%20be%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-middle-age-40-savings-careers-kids-boomers-gen-z-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20miserable%20era%20of%20life%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Is%20the%20problem%20that%20talking%20about%20it%20too%20much%20would%20just%20be%20depressing%3F%20Gerhardt%20shoots%20down%20my%20thesis%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20kind%20of%20on%20brand%20that%20Gen%20X%20is%20overlooked%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Gerhardt%2C%20who%20is%20also%20the%20author%20of%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BGentelligence%3A%20The%20Revolutionary%20Approach%20to%20Leading%20an%20Intergenerational%20Workforce.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20big%20part%20of%20the%20issue%20is%20that%20the%20generation%20never%20became%20the%20most%20dominant%20force%2C%20population-wise.%20Millennials%20surpassed%20boomers%20as%20the%20US's%20largest%20generation%20years%20ago%20%E2%80%94%20Gen%20X%20never%20got%20there.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20Gen%20X%20had%20as%20significant%20of%20a%20ripple%20because%20of%20the%20statistical%20side%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Another%20statistical%20issue%3A%20Gen%20X%20was%20the%20%26quot%3Bleast%20supervised%26quot%3B%20generation%2C%20she%20says.%20In%20many%20households%2C%20they%20were%20the%20first%20cohort%20of%20kids%20to%20have%20both%20parents%20working%20outside%20the%20home%2C%20and%20it%20happened%20at%20a%20time%20before%20they'd%20figured%20out%20day%20care%20entirely%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-feels-she-cant-free-range-parent-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehelicopter%20parenting%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20in%20vogue.%20This%20meant%20many%20Gen%20Xers%20had%20to%20be%20more%20independent%20and%20autonomous.%20There%20was%20no%20tech%20for%20their%20parents%20to%20track%20them%20or%20cellphones%20to%20even%20reach%20them.%20Gen%20X%20kids%20were%20expected%20to%20watch%20TV%20after%20school%20and%20put%20dinner%20in%20the%20oven%20before%20Mom%20and%20Dad%20got%20home.%20They%20were%20the%20%26quot%3Bsupporting%20actors%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20family%2C%20Gerhardt%20says%2C%20not%20the%20focal%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJean%20Twenge%2C%20the%20Gen%20X%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BGenerations%3A%20The%20Real%20Differences%20Between%20Gen%20Z%2C%20Millennials%2C%20Gen%20X%2C%20Boomers%2C%20and%20Silents%20%E2%80%94%20and%20What%20They%20Mean%20for%20America's%20Future%2C%26quot%3B%20tells%20me%20many%20people%20of%20her%20generation%20say%20they%20don't%20feel%20as%20distinctive%20as%20the%20groups%20above%20or%20below%20them.%20Gen%20X's%20psychological%20profile%20tracks%20a%20shift%20across%20generations%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20you%20look%20at%2C%20say%2C%20increases%20in%20positive%20self-views%20and%20individualism%20that%20grew%20steadily%20from%20boomers%20to%20Gen%20Xers%20to%20millennials.%26quot%3B%20Citing%20the%20American%20Freshman%20Survey%2C%20which%20tracks%20the%20attitudes%20of%20incoming%20college%20freshmen%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Twenge%20notes%20that%20from%20boomers%20to%20Gen%20X%20to%20millennials%2C%20young%20people%20have%20become%20more%20focused%20on%20their%20financial%20well-being%20than%20developing%20a%20meaningful%20philosophy%20of%20life%20and%20have%20become%20likelier%20to%20think%20they're%20above%20average.%20Gen%20X%20was%20the%20transitional%20phase%20from%20one%20mindset%20to%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20dynamic%20has%20left%20Gen%20X%20with%20a%20sort%20of%20generational%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-middle-child-syndrome-true-traits-2017-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emiddle-child%20syndrome%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20feel%20overlooked%20and%20stuck%20between%20self-centered%20boomer%20parents%20above%20them%20and%20perhaps%20even%20more%20self-centered%20up-and-comer%20millennials%20behind%20them.%20But%20they're%20also%20good%20at%20figuring%20stuff%20out%20on%20their%20own%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20them%20say%20they'd%20really%20rather%20be%20left%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20super%20proud%20of%20how%20independent%20and%20resourceful%20we%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20Mantz%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ambivalent%20attitude%20Gen%20X%20embodies%20is%20appealing.%20Part%20of%20Salmon's%20Gen%20X%20routine%20is%20that%20the%20generation's%20slogan%20is%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20can%20be%20empowering%20but%20also%20presents%20problems%20at%20work%20and%20for%20people%20just%20trying%20to%20muddle%20through%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Xers%20were%20the%20first%20generation%20to%20reject%20the%20baby%20boomer%20work%20ethic%20and%20rat%20race.%20There's%20a%20reason%20movies%20such%20as%20%26quot%3BThe%20Breakfast%20Club%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BSlackers%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BFerris%20Bueller's%20Day%20Off%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BReality%20Bites%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BOffice%20Space%26quot%3B%20have%20come%20to%20epitomize%20them.%20That's%20good%20in%20that%20there's%20more%20to%20life%20than%20work%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20difficult%20when%20there's%20a%20super-hungry%20generation%20coming%20up%20right%20behind%20you.%20As%20much%20as%20millennials%20prioritize%20work-life%20balance%2C%20they%20also%20want%20to%20get%20ahead%2C%20and%20their%20employers%20have%20been%20happy%20to%20help%20them%20get%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20millennials%20came%20to%20the%20workplace%2C%20they%20brought%20that%20hustle%20culture%20of%20you%20work%20hard%20and%20you%20go%20for%20it%2C%20anything's%20possible%20for%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Gerhardt%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20businesses%20created%20fast-track%20programs%20to%20get%20millennials%20into%20leadership%2C%20which%20often%20leapfrogged%20the%20Gen%20Xers%20in%20the%20room%20for%20some%20positions.%20It's%20left%20Gen%20X%20in%20a%20mediator%20role%20within%20the%20hierarchy%20and%20in%20a%20weird%20limbo.%20Given%20their%20age%2C%20Gen%20Xers%20do%20occupy%20the%20C-suite%20%E2%80%94%20about%20half%20of%20Fortune%20500%20CEOs%20are%20Gen%20Xers%20%E2%80%94%20but%20millennials%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.glassdoor.com%2Fblog%2Fworklife-trends-2025-midyear-check-in%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enow%20make%20up%20the%20largest%20share%20of%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20workforce%20overall.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Flifestyle%2Fcareers%2Fgen-x-business-leadership-executives-d74ca6ad%3Fmod%3Dhp_lead_pos11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20notes%2C%20people%20in%20their%2050s%20are%20losing%20share%20of%20CEO%20spots%20in%20the%20Russell%203000.%20Many%20Gen%20Xers%20feel%20like%20they're%20stuck%20with%20a%20boomer%20executive%20who%20won't%20retire%20or%20a%20millennial%20young%20gun%20who%20shot%20to%20the%20front%20of%20the%20line.%20They're%20the%20translators%20between%20the%20old%20and%20the%20young%2C%20trying%20to%20find%20common%20ground.%20It's%20worth%20pointing%20out%20that%20we%20haven't%20had%20a%20Gen%20X%20president%20yet%2C%20either%20%E2%80%94%20the%20cohort%20is%20more%20of%20a%20victim%20of%20America's%20political%20gerontocracy%20problem%20than%20anyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMantz%20says%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20she%20started%20her%20community%20for%20Gen%20X%20women%20was%20to%20try%20to%20get%20them%20to%20make%20a%20little%20more%20noise%20and%20get%20themselves%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-ceos-boomers-era-over-kamala-harris-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epositions%20of%20power%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20despite%20their%20low-key%20inclinations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20having%20to%20shift%20gears.%20We%20are%20being%20forgotten.%20We're%20being%20taken%20for%20granted%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20such%20a%20strong%20and%20steady%20force%20at%20work%2C%20and%20if%20we%20don't%20start%20changing%20the%20way%20we%20amplify%20our%20generation%2C%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20overlooked.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Xers%20also%20aren't%20particularly%20happy%2C%20and%20again%2C%20not%20just%20because%20they're%20middle-aged.%20Frank%20Infurna%2C%20a%20psychology%20professor%20at%20Arizona%20State%20University%2C%20tells%20me%20that%20Gen%20Xers%20in%20the%20US%20are%20reporting%20higher%20levels%20of%20loneliness%2C%20more%20depressive%20symptoms%2C%20and%20poorer%20physical%20health%20than%20other%20generations.%20He%20says%20their%20cognition%20is%20worse%2C%20too.%20He%20chalks%20it%20up%20to%20a%20variety%20of%20factors.%20Gen%20X%20started%20working%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-social-security-gen-z-millennials-uncertainty-fears-pensions-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etransition%20from%20pensions%20to%20401(k)s%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20the%20onus%20for%20retirement%20savings%20switched%20from