rm%20video%20service%2C%20which%20allowed%20users%20to%20create%20and%20upload%206-second%20videos%2C%20was%20owned%20by%20then-Twitter%20shortly%20after%20its%202012%20founding%20until%20its%20shuttering%20in%202017.%20It%20was%20the%20source%20of%20many%20early%20viral%20videos%20and%20the%20subject%20of%20numerous%20compilations%20of%20%26quot%3Bthe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwatch-best-vines-of-all-time-2016-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebest%20Vines%20of%20all%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Grok%20Imagine%20offers%20a%20new%20AI%20spin%20on%20short-form%20clips%2C%20Musk%20also%20appears%20to%20be%20eyeing%20a%20comeback%20for%20Vine%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBtw%2C%20we%20recently%20found%20the%20Vine%20video%20archive%20(thought%20it%20had%20been%20deleted)%20and%20are%20working%20on%20restoring%20user%20access%2C%20so%20you%20can%20post%20them%20if%20you%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20added%20in%20his%20Saturday%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20whether%20restoring%20the%20Vine%20archive%20would%20allow%20users%20to%20access%20their%20old%20accounts%20or%20if%20it%20would%20be%20a%20temporary%20measure%20allowing%20access%20to%20old%20files%20from%20the%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20and%20representatives%20for%20X%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20access%20to%20Grok%20Imagine%20is%20being%20slowly%20rolled%20out%20to%20subscribers%20of%20the%20chatbot's%20%2430-monthly%20premium%20tier%2C%20SuperGrok%2C%20though%20any%20user%20of%20X%20can%20sign%20up%20to%20be%20added%20to%20the%20waitlist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-grok-new-image-generator-restore-vine-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1754180672000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider