EO%20John%20Stankey%20is%20serious%20about%20the%20company's%20cultural%20evolution.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20a%20memo%20to%20managers%20on%20Friday%2C%20he%20detailed%20his%20expectations%20for%20the%20company's%20future.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHis%20message%20reflects%20broader%20trends%20in%20corporate%20culture.%20Here%20are%20the%20top%205%20takeaways.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECEOs%20are%20done%20mincing%20words.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAT%26amp%3BT%20CEO%20John%20Stankey%20didn't%20hold%20back%20in%20a%20Friday%20message%20to%20managers%20at%20the%20140%2C000-person%20company%3A%20%26quot%3BCommit%20to%20adjusting%20your%20own%20behaviors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStankey's%20message%20comes%20about%20seven%20months%20after%20the%20company%20issued%20a%20strict%20return-to-office%20mandate%20and%20amid%20what%20the%20CEO%20described%20as%20a%20longer-term%20cultural%20shift%20underway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202%2C500-word%20memo%20is%20a%20rare%20and%20detailed%20window%20into%20a%20CEO's%20thinking%20during%20a%20period%20of%20transition.%20It%20offers%20valuable%20insight%20for%20workers%20beyond%20just%20AT%26amp%3BT%20employees%20and%20reveals%20how%20a%20large%2C%20legacy%20company%20is%20working%20to%20adapt%20and%20innovate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20published%20the%20full%202%2C500-word%20memo%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fatt-ceo-john-stankey-email-employee-feedback-survey-rto-policy-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20our%20top%20five%20takeaways%20on%20how%20Stankey's%20message%20reflects%20broader%20shifts%20in%20corporate%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2233803eca-0750-451c-b5bf-32bbf99e2582%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECEOs%20are%20done%20sugarcoating%20change%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tone%20of%20Stankey's%20memo%20is%20direct%2C%20reflecting%20a%20broader%20shift%20in%20how%20corporate%20executives%20are%20communicating%20to%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20a%20self-directed%2C%20virtual%2C%20or%20hybrid%20work%20schedule%20is%20essential%20for%20you%20to%20manage%20your%20career%20aspirations%20and%20life%20challenges%2C%20you%20will%20have%20a%20difficult%20time%20aligning%20your%20priorities%20with%20those%20of%20the%20company%20and%20the%20culture%20we%20aim%20to%20establish%2C%26quot%3B%20Stankey%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20sort%20of%20candid%20communication%20has%20become%20increasingly%20common%20among%20executives%20as%20they%20work%20to%20make%20change%2C%20whether%20return-to-office%20mandates%20or%20efforts%20to%20adapt%20to%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-andy-jassy-rto-office-policy-employee-jobs-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etold%20his%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202023%20that%20if%20they%20didn't%20embrace%20working%20in%20the%20office%2C%20they%20may%20not%20have%20a%20future%20at%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20past%20the%20time%20to%20disagree%20and%20commit%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20at%20the%20time.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20you%20can't%20disagree%20and%20commit%2C%20I%20also%20understand%20that%2C%20but%20it's%20probably%20not%20going%20to%20work%20out%20for%20you%20at%20Amazon%20because%20we%20are%20going%20back%20to%20the%20office%20at%20least%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20right%20for%20all%20of%20our%20teammates%20to%20be%20in%20three%20days%20a%20week%20and%20for%20people%20to%20refuse%20to%20do%20so.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20later%20expanded%20the%20mandate%20to%20five%20days%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-jassy-ceos-warning-workers-ai-bring-massive-change-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJassy%20didn't%20hold%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20memo%20posted%20to%20the%20company's%20website%20in%20June.%20He%20said%20workers%20should%20expect%20AI%20to%20impact%20staffing%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20we%20expect%20that%20this%20will%20reduce%20our%20total%20corporate%20workforce%20as%20we%20get%20efficiency%20gains%20from%20using%20AI%20extensively%20across%20the%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227c2355fb-884e-4fe9-80bb-88377c773260%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompany%20culture%20is%20no%20longer%20about%20loyalty%2C%20tenure%2C%20or%20family.%20It's%20about%20performance.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAT%26amp%3BT%20is%20a%20nearly%20150-year-old%20company%20that%20has%20long%20embodied%20a%20culture%20that%20celebrates%20loyalty%20and%20tenure.%20Focus%20on%20those%20values%2C%20however%2C%20is%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20past%2C%20Stankey%20said.%20He%20was%20upfront%20about%20this%20change%20in%20Friday's%20memo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20shift%20can%20be%20characterized%20as%20moving%20away%20from%20an%20orientation%20on%20hierarchy%20and%20familial%20cultural%20norms%20and%20towards%20a%20more%20externally%20focused%20and%20competitive%20market-based%20culture%2C%26quot%3B%20Stankey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20reflects%20the%20performance%20vibe%20that%20has%20become%20so%20prominent%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20in%20the%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmy%20Coleman%2C%20Microsoft's%20chief%20people%20officer%2C%20wrote%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-email-details-new-policies-cull-low-performers-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20message%20to%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20April%20that%20the%20company%20was%20introducing%20new%20tools%20to%20improve%20performance%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%2C%20we're%20rolling%20out%20new%20and%20enhanced%20tools%20to%20help%20you%20accelerate%20high%20performance%20and%20swiftly%20address%20low%20performance%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BOur%20goal%20is%20to%20create%20a%20globally%20consistent%20and%20transparent%20experience%20for%20employees%20and%20managers%20(subject%20to%20local%20laws%20and%20consultation).%20These%20tools%20will%20also%20help%20foster%20a%20culture%20of%20accountability%20and%20growth%20by%20enabling%20you%20to%20address%20performance%20challenges%20with%20clarity%20and%20empathy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStankey%20said%20performance%20would%20be%20employees'%20best%20metric%20for%20longevity%20at%20the%20company%20moving%20forward%2C%20and%20encouraged%20staff%20to%20get%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20change%20like%20this%20is%20difficult%20and%20can%20be%20unsettling%20for%20some.%20However%2C%20as%20General%20Eric%20Shinseki%20so%20eloquently%20stated%2C%20'If%20you%20dislike%20change%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20dislike%20irrelevance%20even%20more.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224cc530cf-365d-4c5c-9637-1625a87cb4a4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEmployees%20need%20to%20carry%20their%20own%20weight%2C%20and%20management%20is%20watching%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20new%20era%20at%20AT%26amp%3BT%2C%20managers%20will%20have%20a%20new%20tool%20for%20evaluating%20whether%20employees%20are%20really%20meeting%20the%20demands%20of%20their%20job%3A%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20addition%20to%20information%20garnered%20from%20performance%20reviews%2C%20peer%20feedback%2C%20assessments%2C%20work%20history%2C%20and%20certifications%20(to%20name%20a%20few)%2C%20we%20analyze%20patterns%20of%20behaviors%20from%20broad%20cohorts%20(aggregated%20data)%2C%26quot%3B%20Stankey%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThis%20allows%20leaders%20to%20identify%20behaviors%20that%20are%20obvious%20outliers%2C%20supplemented%20with%20the%20broadest%20set%20of%20information%20available%2C%20to%20determine%20if%20the%20behavior%20being%20evaluated%20is%20consistent%20with%20our%20stated%20priorities%20and%20employment%20expectations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutliers%20in%20the%20data%20will%20be%20identified%20and%20dealt%20with%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAddressing%20these%20exceptions%20is%20important%20to%20ensure%20we're%20fair%20to%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20employees%20who%20support%20their%20colleagues%20and%20deliver%20for%20the%20organization%20every%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20Stankey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20took%20a%20different%20approach%20to%20the%20same%20goal%20by%20cutting%20down%20on%20managers%20to%20%26quot%3Bflatten%26quot%3B%20the%20organization%20and%20push%20individuals%20to%20pull%20their%20weight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20do%20this%20work%20well%2C%20it%20will%20increase%20our%20teammates'%20ability%20to%20move%20fast%2C%20clarify%20and%20invigorate%20their%20sense%20of%20ownership%2C%20drive%20decision-making%20closer%20to%20the%20front%20lines%20where%20it%20most%20impacts%20customers%20(and%20the%20business)%2C%20decrease%20bureaucracy%2C%20and%20strengthen%20our%20organizations'%20ability%20to%20make%20customers'%20lives%20better%20and%20easier%20every%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225b749ce1-fd09-4ab0-9ea9-f7f58639b67a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20companies%20see%20returning%20to%20the%20office%20as%20necessary%20to%20compete%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStankey%20said%20AT%26amp%3BT's%20push%20for%20change%20is%20driven%20by%20%26quot%3Befforts%20that%20require%20inter-departmental%20collaboration%20and%20coordination.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20%26quot%3Bcollaboration%20and%20predictable%20presence%20improve%20each%20team's%20ability%20to%20execute%20effectively%20on%20large%2C%20complex%20projects%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20To%20achieve%20that%2C%20employees%20must%20%26quot%3Bwork%20in%20person%2C%20together%2C%20during%20common%20hours.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20that%20working%20together%20in%20an%20office%20is%20ultimately%20better%20for%20the%20company's%20success%20is%20a%20growing%20belief%20among%20executives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarbucks%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-return-to-office-corporate-employees-4-days-a-week-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBrian%20Niccol%20told%20staff%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20email%20last%20month%20that%20returning%20to%20the%20office%20allows%20employees%20to%20%26quot%3Bshare%20ideas%20more%20effectively%2C%20creatively%20solve%20hard%20problems%2C%20and%20move%20much%20faster.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20understand%20not%20everyone%20will%20agree%20with%20this%20approach%2C%26quot%3B%20Niccol%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BBut%20as%20a%20company%20built%20on%20human%20connection%2C%20and%20given%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20turnaround%20ahead%2C%20we%20believe%20this%20is%20the%20right%20path%20for%20Starbucks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22844b573d-69d1-4a25-9f71-9a5c3eb58eba%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EReturning%20to%20the%20office%20isn't%20always%20without%20its%20problems%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20employees%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fatt-begins-5-days-office-mandate-desks-parking-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAT%26amp%3BT's%20return-to-office%20push%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20caused%20some%20practical%20problems%2C%20including%20a%20lack%20of%20desks%20and%20parking%20spaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20employee%20at%20the%20company's%20Atlanta%20office%20said%20the%20company's%20working%20environment%20had%20%26quot%3Bdeteriorated%26quot%3B%20as%20more%20employees%20returned.%20Two%20others%20said%20finding%20parking%20in%20a%20timely%20manner%20had%20been%20a%20challenge%20for%20themselves%20and%20for%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStankey%20addressed%20these%20complaints%20in%20his%20message%20in%20a%20section%20titled%20%26quot%3BCapabilities%20to%20do%20your%20job.%26quot%3B%20He%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20deserve%20tools%2C%20processes%2C%20and%20capabilities%20that%20help%20you%20serve%20our%20customers%20effectively%2C%